data.enText: a magazine that is published every week, month, etc., especially one that is concerned with an academic subject

tr: a publication that appears at fixed intervals
happening or recurring at regular intervals
example: the periodic appearance of the seventeen-year locust

value.def: Periodicals are magazines, especially serious or academic ones, that are published at regular intervals.

example.ex: The walls would be lined with books and periodicals.
example.tran: 这几面墙会摆放书籍和期刊。

value.def: Periodical events or situations happen occasionally, at fairly regular intervals.

example.ex: She made periodical visits to her dentist.

value.tran: 间发性的；定期的；周期的

example.ex: Meetings are held periodically to monitor progress on the case...
example.tran: 定期举行会议以监督案件的进展。

example.ex: Police were periodically patrolling the area.
example.tran: 警察定时在这一地区巡逻。
